    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nthere is no easy way to take over all the keyboard inputs from nvim, and remapping all possible keys for a 'custom' mode is not efficient.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nfrom what i know, there is no such equivalent in neovim to tmux's key-table.\r\nwith it, users can implement their custom mode easily. to me, i want to use it to add an 'IME' mode to nvim as a frontend of librime; and as not nvim is trying to be 'Text editor as a platform'. i think that's worth it to have a consideration.\r\n\r\n### more contexts\r\nit's [this article](https://alexherbo2.github.io/config/tmux/make-tmux-modal/) that inspired me, and my past uses of hydra.nvim, nvim-treesitter's incremental selection.",
